        "@id": "https://ww1.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=7181"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Luka Sulic"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Luka Sulic, the virtuoso cellist celebrated worldwide for his captivating performances and distinctive artistry, will be performing in Montréal. Best known as a founding member of the international phenomenon 2Cellos, Sulic has reached millions of listeners with his ability to blend classical mastery and contemporary energy. Together with Stjepan Hauser, he brought the cello into the global spotlight, reinventing rock, pop, and classical hits with a fresh and daring approach that appealed to audiences of all ages. His success with 2Cellos included sold-out tours on every continent and collaborations with legends like Sir Elton John, making him one of the most recognizable cellists of his generation.<br><br>\n \nWith LIFE (2024), his first album as a composer, arranger, and soloist, Sulic reveals a more intimate side of his artistry. The project is both heartfelt and diverse, reflecting his passion for creative freedom and his wish to share universal emotions through music. Drawing inspiration from great classical composers as well as modern influences, the album explores themes of love, struggle, and renewal. It demonstrates Sulic's belief that music should remain open, inclusive, and meaningful, capable of touching listeners regardless of their background.<br><br>\n \nOn stage, Sulic transforms this vision into an unforgettable live experience. His playing combines sensitivity, technical brilliance, and a natural connection with the audience. Whether in stadiums filled alongside Elton John or in prestigious concert halls such as Amsterdam's Concertgebouw and Vienna's Musikverein, his performances balance elegance with authenticity and leave audiences deeply moved.<br><br>\n \nDon't miss the opportunity to experience Luka Sulic live in Montréal, an evening where the cello takes center stage, leaving a lasting impression long after the final note.\n</p>\n<iframe width='560' height='315' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/wc_diVAauzs?si=A4bOHGgIAzLqv8C1' title='YouTube video player' frameborder='0' allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share' referrerpolicy='strict-origin-when-cross-origin' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n<style>\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){\niframe{width:100%;}\n}\n</style>"
      }
    ],
